    <script type="text/javascript">
        $(document).ready(function() {
            $('.select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').hide();
            
            $('.tab', '#section6').click(function() {
                $('.tab, .tab-content', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $(this).addClass('current');
                $('.tab-content[data-id=' + $(this).data('id') + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($(this).index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').addClass('current');
                chkContentHeight();
            });

            $('.tab-select', '#section6').change(function() {
                $('.tab, .tab-content', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab[data-id=' + $(this).val() + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-content[data-id=' + $(this).val() + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div:nth-child(' +  ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.select .select-container div', '#section6').show();
                $('.select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').hide();
                chkContentHeight();
            });

            $('.record-slider', '#section6').Slider({
                slides: '.record-item',
                maxSlide: 1,
                swipeControl: true,
                skipBoundary: true,
                infiniteLoop: true
            });

            function chkContentHeight() {
                $('p.description', '#section6').each(function() {
                    if($(this).height() > 160) {
                        $(this).parent().addClass('more');
                    }
                });
            }
            chkContentHeight();

            $('.record-item article button.view-more', '#section6').click(function() {
                $(this).hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.view-less').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.description').hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.content').show();
            });
            $('.record-item article button.view-less', '#section6').click(function() {
                $(this).hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.view-more').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.description').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.content').hide();
            });
        });
    </script>
</section>
<section id="section7" data-total="10">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
            <h2 class="colour2">What's New at QBS?</h2>
            <span class="bg-colour1"></span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="record-slider">
        <div class="slider-container">
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="132">
                        <time>25/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our Year 6 students took a giant leap into the future this week! As part of their How We Organise Ourselves unit of inquiry, students and parents teamed up to play the Global Goal Games.<br><br>This immersive card-based simulation transported our learners to the year 2030, challenging them to navigate the "real world" and meet the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). From ending poverty to protecting our planet, the stakes couldn't have been higher!<br><br>A huge thank you to the parents who joined us in this mission. Together, we’re making sure we leave a better planet than we found it!<br><br>#esfqbs #globalgoalsgame #Year6 #IBPYP #futureleaders #learningthroughplay</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/2c1d5ced849bd15c0533a9631f91be0b.jpg" alt="641851166_18109254148778564_7445000107337861855_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="131">
                        <time>20/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>Wishing everyone a Happy Year of the Horse! May your year be filled with:<br><br>✨ Prosperity that keeps pace with your hard work.<br>✨ Success that knows no hurdles.<br>✨ Joy at every turn.<br><br>Kung Hei Fat Choi - 恭喜发财<br><br>#esfqbs #YearOfTheHorse #cny2026</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/e59daec224c9646073e5efac5bdb2b42.jpg" alt="637048586_18108778843778564_1708267830784499789_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="130">
                        <time>13/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>We had an absolutely unforgettable last day before our Chinese New Year break, filled with energy, tradition, and incredible talent. The campus was buzzing from start to finish!<br><br>🧧 Wishing our entire community a prosperous, healthy, and happy Chinese New Year! Enjoy the well-deserved break.<br><br>#esfqbs #cny2026 #yearofthehorse2026</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/8ebf8e9bb02d966d561a5a8425800615.jpg" alt="629614397_18108157192778564_1369367854375969058_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="129">
                        <time>12/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>The annual Chinese New Year collaboration between Chinese International School (@cishk) and Quarry Bay School once again brought our two school communities together to welcome the Year of the Horse. This tradition featured a joint visual arts project sharing ongoing appreciation for how art unites us across borders and backgrounds. <br>The opening ceremony was a joyful occasion attended by students from both schools, along with Ms Gardon, Principal of Chinese International School, Mr Cogbill, Vice Principal of Quarry Bay School, and the visual arts teachers. <br><br>#esfqbs #cishk #artscollaboration #cny2026 #yearofthehorse</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/87cb834a0506c373237e02126498a24b.jpg" alt="626293469_18108071209778564_7526821970157933333_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="128">
                        <time>10/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>✨ Flashback to an unforgettable Centenary Fair! ✨<br><br>A massive thank you to our amazing PTA Coordinator and her tireless team of volunteers. <br><br>This event showed the strength of the QBS community. From the stage to the stalls, it was an evening to remember.<br><br>To everyone who baked, performed, volunteered, entertained or simply showed up to share the joy—thank you for making our school such a vibrant place.<br><br>#esfqbs #QBSCentenaryFair #qbspta #CommunitySpirit #weareqbs</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/55e66dcfeb2d0c54ccc3068a6229d89f.jpg" alt="626257514_18107924851778564_6610700546792938729_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="127">
                        <time>05/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>QBS is transforming as we get ready for the PTA Centenary Fair tomorrow! We are buzzing with excitement to celebrate 100 years of community, history, and fun. <br><br>A massive shout-out to our incredible PTA and parent volunteers who have been working tirelessly behind the scenes to make this magic happen. <br><br>See you all tomorrow—let’s make history together!<br><br>#esfqbs #centenialfair #communityevent</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/d20dfdcdbaea04446e2da680251c7db1.jpg" alt="625896646_18107487526778564_1079919448185570595_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="126">
                        <time>29/01/2026</time>
                        <h3>QBS got a hands-on look at the vibrant world of Cantonese Opera today. <br>Our students learned how instruments and percussion set the heartbeat of the play, the symbolism behind accessories and costumes, and most importantly, they witnessed the immense rigour required to master the "four basic skills": singing, acting, delivery of spoken lines, and martial arts.<br>We now have a new appreciation for the hard work and heart that keep this beautiful tradition alive.<br><br>A huge thank you to One Table Two Chairs Charitable Foundation for sharing their passion and showing us that behind every graceful gesture lies years of dedicated practice!<br><br>#esfqbs #cantoneseopera #1table2chairs #learningthrougharts #culturalheritage</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/ebddc20c90718daee97a766d8fcbfb0d.jpg" alt="624686241_18106648972778564_7527765642478338137_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="125">
                        <time>22/01/2026</time>
                        <h3>QBS were thrilled to welcome UK-based artist Caroline Cleave today as our Artist in Residence. Caroline spent an inspiring session with our Year 5 students, guiding them in creating beautiful, individually unique koi carp. Her warmth and expertise were a hit with the students, who loved the opportunity to learn from such a talented professional.<br><br>This visit was extra special for our community, as Caroline is the sister of our own Principal. It was a privilege to have her share her artistic passion with us, and we are incredibly proud of the stunning work our students produced under her mentorship. <br><br>Thank you, Caroline!<br><br>#esfqbs #artistinresidence #learningthrougharts</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/cadf9fd870ea331f5975312f89194bb8.jpg" alt="619265003_18106002823778564_6086421426463481758_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="124">
                        <time>15/01/2026</time>
                        <h3>Big congrats to Karisse and Avery for winning the HKPSSA Table Tennis Championship today! The skill level, focus, and sportsmanship they displayed were truly impressive. A huge thank you to all the participants and volunteers who made the event run smoothly.<br>#esfqbs #hkpssatabletennischampionship #learningthroughsport #weareqbs</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/d235a7a734fc4d71bf0469f5738b8cde.jpg" alt="613492380_18105367420778564_3859264923145846269_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="123">
                        <time>09/01/2026</time>
                        <h3>This Saturday, 10 January, marks the official anniversary of our 1926 opening. <br>Today, we held a special birthday assembly, and all year groups participated in various activities and challenges based on the number 100. <br>Earlier in the week, students also collaborated to create a spectacular piece of aerial photography spelling out 'QBS 100.' <br><br>Happy Birthday, QBS! Stay tuned, as more celebration events will be announced soon.<br><br>#esfqbs #celebrating100years #happybirthdayQBS #weareqbs #qbs100</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/73f11d70abb18e7970e5c79746becf6a.jpg" alt="610740348_18104861113778564_8655851017989591434_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="132">
